Edge cases for kd
================

	>>> import kd

No more than two args on command line

	>>> kd.parse_command_line(['alan','was','here'])
	Traceback (most recent call last):
	...
	ValueError: Usage: kd directory [sub-dir]

And no less than 1

	>>> kd.parse_command_line([])
	('', None)

Directories found must be real

	>>> kd.find_dir('rubbish')
	Traceback (most recent call last):
	...
	ValueError: rubbish is not a directory

Can send a blank as the sub-dir

	>>> kd.find_dir('/usr/local','')
	<path '/usr/local'>

Same effect if sub-dir is not found
	>>> kd.find_dir('/usr/local','this_is_not_real')
	<path '/usr/local'>


When main() fails it prints out nothing
	>>> import sys
	>>> sys.argv = [ 'kd', 'no_such_directory' ]
	>>> kd.main()
	1

Cleanup
=======
	>>> sys.argv = []
